# Internationalization (i18n) Requirements

## General Rule

- **Always implement next-intl framework** for all user-facing text
- **Never hardcode text** in components or pages
- **Use translation keys** for all copy
- **Support multiple locales** (en, sv)

## Implementation Pattern

### Server Components

```typescript
import { getTranslations } from 'next-intl/server';

export default async function SettingsPage() {
  const t = await getTranslations('settings');

  return (
    <div className="container mx-auto px-6 py-8">
      <div className="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
        <div className="mb-8">
          <h1 className="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">{t('title')}</h1>
          <p className="text-muted-foreground mb-6">
            {t('settings_description')}
          </p>
        </div>
        {/* Page content */}
      </div>

}
```

### Client Components

```typescript
'use client';
import { useTranslations } from 'next-intl';

export default function UserProfileCard({ user }: UserProfileCardProps) {
  const t = useTranslations('user_profile');

  return (
    <div>
      <h2>{t('profile_title')}</h2>
      <p>{t('member_since', { date: user.createdAt })}</p>
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Examples

